					"linecount" : 4,
					"maxclass" : "comment",
					"numinlets" : 1,
					"numoutlets" : 0,
					"patching_rect" : [ 6.5, 84.0, 738.0, 65.0 ],
					"text" : "Achieving polyphonic synthesis and sampling without clicks is the job of adsr~, as part of its job of generating an ADSR gain  envelope. With voice stealing on, overloading the voices in poly~ can produce clicks as the old voices are suddently shut off . This patch avoids clicks, since  adsr~ implements a quick fade-to-zero before starting the new note. By making the patch MIDI-compatible, notes can have durations that are not predetermined.",
					"textcolor" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ]
				}

			}
